HEADWORD: Parumbilical
<hw>Par`um*bil"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>umbilical</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Near the umbilicus; -- applied especially to one or more small
veins which, in man, connect the portal vein with the epigastric veins
in the front wall of the abdomen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parure</ent>⟦br⟧
